* #pathname expansion
~ #tilde expansion
  #arithmetic expansion
$((expression))
Arithmetic expansion only supports integers(whole numbers, no decimals) but can perform a number of different operations: +-*/%**

{} #brace expansion. 
echo Number {1..5}
echo Number {1,2,4}
mkdir {2007..2010}-0{1.9} {2007..2009}-{10-12}

 #Parameter Expansion

 #Command Substitution: allows us to use the output of a command as an expansion
echo $(ls)
We can use back-quotes instead of the dollar sign and the parentheses:
echo `ls`

Remember, parameter expansion, arithmetic expansion, and command substitution still take place within double quote
